<div class="help-center">
	<h1 class="heading">PRIVACY POLICY</h1>

	<div class="back-link-wrap">
		<a href="/help-center" class="back-link ties">
			<i class="fa fa-chevron-left"></i> BACK TO HELP CENTER
		</a>
	</div>

	<div class="help-center-copy">
		<div class="section">
			<p>
				At Ties.com we are committed to ensuring your privacy as a customer. We do not sell, trade, or rent
				your personal information to others. We are dedicated not only providing you, our customer, with the
				best possible shopping experience, but also to ensuring your complete privacy. Information we
				collect from you is used to process your orders with us and provide for you the best possible
				shopping experience.
			</p>

			<p>
				Ties.com is the sole owner of all personally identifiable information collected via our web site.
				By visiting our website, you are accepting the practices described in this Privacy Policy. Please
				read on for more details about our privacy policy.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Information We Collect and the Uses For It</h3>

			<p>
				When you place an order with Ties.com we will need to know your full name, mailing address, e-mail
				address, phone number, credit card number, and credit card expiration date. This information is used
				to fulfill your order, including payment and shipping, and to notify you of your order status.
			</p>

			<p>
				To ship your order, it will be necessary for us to share your name, address, and telephone number
				with the shipping company of our choice. Shipping companies require this information to deliver your
				products.
			</p>

			<p>
				Upon completion of your order, your credit card information is deleted from our database to ensure
				your protection.
			</p>

			<p>
				We offer a free newsletter through Ties.com used to keep you informed of specials, deliver
				information of interest, and more. To sign up for the newsletter we will ask for your e-mail
				address. We will deliver the newsletter to your e-mail address, and you will have the option to stop
				your receipt of the publication at any time. We only require your e-mail address for the purpose of
				the newsletter, and you will only receive our newsletter if you so choose.
			</p>

			<p>
				We occasionally offer contests and special promotions on our site. In order to take part in these
				opportunities, we will need to gather your name, e-mail address, and mailing address. This
				information is used to notify winners and administer the specific contest or promotion.
			</p>

			<p>
				We may request your participation in online or offline surveys via e-mail, telephone, postal mail,
				or web pages. Surveys are strictly voluntary and your participation and/or answers do not prohibit
				or influence your use of our website. Furthermore, if you do participate in a survey, you may
				decline to answer any question, and all answers are held in strict confidence according to our
				privacy standards. Individually identifiable survey information is for the use of Ties.com only.
				General, aggregate survey results may be shared with third parties. Information you may be asked may
				include, but is not limited to, your name, address, e-mail address, phone number, income, age,
				gender, marital status, type of business, product usage, schooling, and hobbies. Survey data is used
				to enhance Ties.com to provide a better customer experience.
			</p>

			<p>
				When you make purchases at our site, we monitor the information enabling us to better serve you. We
				use the general purchasing information to help us determine what products and services you are most
				interested in. We also keep track of site traffic using log files to help us better determine what
				areas of our site are providing our customers with the greatest value. We use this information to
				fine tune our site and tailor it to you and other visitors to our site.
			</p>

			<p>
				From time to time we may use information we collect from you to notify you of important or exciting
				changes to our website, new or changing services we offer, and other special offers we think may be
				useful to you. If you decide you would rather not receive this information, send us an e-mail
				message and We'll take you off our mailing lists until you inform us otherwise.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Privacy Protection - How It's Done</h3>

			<p>
				The online shopping process at Ties.com is safe and secure. Whenever you are in the process of
				placing an order, accessing personal information, or providing personal information we use a secure
				server. Powerful, industry-standard SSL secure server software provides encryption for all
				information sent between your computer and ours. Additionally, we protect our server and all
				customer data against unauthorized use physically or electronically.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Cookies</h3>

			<p>
				The so-called cookie is a small piece of information that is stored on your computer's hard drive by
				your web browser and which may be accessed by our server. The cookies we provide to your browser do
				not contain any personal information, but they do allow us to provide special services to you while
				you visit our website. Cookies simplify the ordering process by remembering information about you,
				allow the use of the shopping cart function, and enable online ordering.
			</p>

			<p>
				If you do not wish to accept cookies, most browsers allow you to prevent them from being accepted
				and saved to your hard drive. If you choose not to use cookies, you will be unable to place online
				orders at our website.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Do Not Track Headers</h3>

			<p>
				Ties.com itself does not respond to the "Do Not Track" HTTP Header.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Disclosure of Information to Third Parties</h3>

			<p>Ties.com does not currently sell, trade, or rent your personal information to any third parties.</p>

			<p>
				We may merge customer data stored in our database with data from third parties for the purposes of
				enhancing and marketing products and/or services to customers.
			</p>

			<p>
				We may provide aggregate statistics of our users to third parties in reference to traffic patterns,
				numbers of users, sales, and other site and customer information. This information will never
				provide any personally identifiable information on individual users.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Non-Personally Identifiable Information</h3>

			<p>
				This refers to information that does not, by itself, identify you as a specific individual. We
				gather certain information about you based on where you have shopped for on our web site in several
				ways. This information is then compiled and analyzed on both an individual and an aggregate basis.
				Such non-personally identifiable information may include demographics and interest data. We use data
				from Google's Interest-based advertising or 3rd-party audience data (such as age, gender and
				interests) with Google Analytics. We use Google Analytics' Demographic and Interest Reporting Tools
				to figure out the general types of people who visit our store. Additional non-personally
				identifiable information may also include the Web site's Uniform Resource Locator ("URL")
				information as well as your Internet Protocol ("IP") address. A URL is the global address of
				documents and resources on the World Wide Web. An IP address is an identifier for computer or device
				on a Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol ("TCP/IP") network, such as the World Wide Web.
				Networks use the TCP/IP protocol to route or reroute information based on the IP address of the
				destination. In other words, an IP address is a number that is automatically assigned to your
				computer whenever you are surfing the web, which allows web servers to locate and to identify your
				computer. Computers require an IP addresses in order for users to communicate over the Internet.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Notifying You of Changes to the Use of Your Information</h3>

			<p>
				If at some point in the future there is a change to our information usage practices that affects
				your personal information, we will post the relevant changes on our website. You should check this
				posted privacy statement periodically for changes.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Contacting You</h3>

			<p>
				We will send you e-mail messages during the processing of your order to verify your order placement
				and to notify you of its status. If there is a problem with your order, we may also contact you via
				e-mail, phone, or fax to notify you of the problem and solution. We may also contact you via e-mail,
				postal mail, phone, or fax regarding questions or comments you have regarding our website or our
				business. Surveys and post-sale satisfaction questions may also be administered via e-mail, postal
				mail, phone, or fax to help us better serve our customers.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Contacting Us</h3>

			<p>
				You may contact us with any concerns you may have at 1 (800) 289-2843 or via e-mail at
				customerservice@ties.com. You may also send us correspondence via postal mail to the following
				address:
			</p>

			<p>
				Ties.com Customer Service<br/>
				10372 Stanford Ave, Suite Q<br/>
				Garden Grove, CA 92840
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="section">
			<h3 class="section-heading">Summary</h3>

			<p>
				At Ties.com your privacy is one of our top priorities. We realize that your personal information is
				very important to you, just as you are very important to us. It is necessary for us to collect
				certain private information from you in order to make shopping at our site possible, however, we do
				not collect more information than is necessary nor do we use that information in ways other than
				what it was given to us for and the uses posted above.
			</p>

			<p>
				This Privacy Policy for Ties.com as stated herein is effective from July 1st, 2007.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


